1: Reverse a string without using built-in
 reverse

Time Complexity: O(n)

âœ… Method 1: Using Loop
def reverse_string(s):
    rev = ""
    for char in s:
        rev = char + rev
    return rev

# Example
text = "DataEngineer"
print(reverse_string(text))

âœ… Method 2: Using While Loop
def reverse_string(s):
    rev = ""
    i = len(s) - 1
    
    while i >= 0:
        rev += s[i]
        i -= 1
        
    return rev

# Example
print(reverse_string("Python"))

âœ… Method 3: Using Recursion
def reverse_string(s):
    if len(s) == 0:
        return s
    return reverse_string(s[1:]) + s[0]

# Example
print(reverse_string("SQLPython"))

========== By using Built-in method=========
âœ… Method 1: Using Slicingdef reverse_string(s):
    return s[::-1]

# Example
text = "DataEngineer"
print(reverse_string(text))

âœ… Method 2: Using reversed()def reverse_string(s):
    return "".join(reversed(s))

# Example
print(reverse_string("Python"))

âœ… Method 3: One-Line
text = "SQLPython"
print(text[::-1])


